Mating With Predation Summary

Courtship:

Note: Box == Treatment (Predator vs.Control)

courtship_model1 <- lmer(court_prop ~ Box + Replicate + TempCent + HumCent + BPCent + (1|Date), data = courtship_for_analysis)
summary(courtship_model1)
## Linear mixed model fit by REML ['lmerMod']
## Formula: court_prop ~ Box + Replicate + TempCent + HumCent + BPCent +  
##     (1 | Date)
##    Data: courtship_for_analysis
## 
## REML criterion at convergence: 71.9
## 
## Scaled residuals: 
##      Min       1Q   Median       3Q      Max 
## -1.81892 -0.79151 -0.09858  0.86998  2.11869 
## 
## Random effects:
##  Groups   Name        Variance Std.Dev.
##  Date     (Intercept) 0.00000  0.0000  
##  Residual             0.08755  0.2959  
## Number of obs: 128, groups:  Date, 6
## 
## Fixed effects:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value
## (Intercept)  0.55832    0.06939   8.046
## BoxPredator -0.03946    0.05250  -0.751
## Replicate   -0.05910    0.02849  -2.075
## TempCent    -0.05437    0.07224  -0.753
## HumCent     -0.06237    0.04594  -1.358
## BPCent       0.27518    0.13173   2.089
## 
## Correlation of Fixed Effects:
##             (Intr) BxPrdt Replct TmpCnt HumCnt
## BoxPredator -0.404                            
## Replicate   -0.846  0.031                     
## TempCent    -0.289  0.032  0.332              
## HumCent      0.233  0.016 -0.286 -0.601       
## BPCent      -0.122  0.011  0.141  0.307 -0.793
plot(effect("Box", courtship_model1), main = "Proportion of Male Time Courting of Immature Female in 900 Seconds",
     ylab = "Proportion of Time courting (sec)", xlab = "Treatment")

Copulation Proportion
